__NAME__ purpose
specify log granularity treshold
__END__

__NAME__ see also
SysLog
__END__

__NAME__ synopsis
<arg choice='plain'><replaceable>integer_treshold</replaceable></arg>
__END__


__NAME__ description
This directive specifies the desired log granularity treshold.
__END__

__NAME__ notes
This directive is currently largely unused in the code. The only two 
<option>priority_integer</option>s used are <literal>4</literal> and
<literal>5</literal>.
</para><para>
When &conf-Logging; is set to a value greater than
<literal>4</literal>, HTTP headers are logged.
When &conf-Logging; is set to a value greater than
<literal>5</literal>, contents of the POST &glos-HTML; form submission
are logged as well.
__END__

__NAME__ example: Logging HTTP headers and POST data
<programlisting>
Logging 6
</programlisting>
__END__


__NAME__ example: Disabling __FILENAME__
<programlisting>
Logging 0
</programlisting>
__END__

